&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content - Contact - Conduct&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content&lt;/strong&gt;  child being exposed to inappropriate or harmful material that can be distressing and frightening and can influence their behaviours, activities, the way they behave towards each other and how they feel about themselves. Information is not individually targeted towards the child but things like advertising and online games may be marketed towards their age group. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact&lt;/strong&gt; Adult initiated online activity can result in physical contact  such as harassment or sexual abuse. Online activity also used to radicalise young people and influence them ideologically.&#160; Contact also refers to the obtaining of their data and possibly being blackmailed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conduct&lt;/strong&gt;  The use of social media can influence children and young people&amp;apos;s behaviour and activities and often towards each other. In some instances. Some children and young people they will be placing themselves at risk of breaking the law.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Child Sexual Abuse  Modern Technology&lt;u&gt; &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technology assisted grooming &lt;/strong&gt; perpetrators forging a close relationship with a victim via technology in order to gain the child&amp;apos;s compliance in and secrecy around subsequent sexual abuse (for example, the perpetrator shows care and interest in a child online who subsequently &amp;apos;falls in love&amp;apos; and consents to online and/or offline sexual activity despite the perpetrator being an adult and/or coercive and/or the child feeling uncomfortable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sexual images&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt; created consensually but shared non-consensually &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;- for example, a young person shares images with a romantic partner, the relationship ends and those images are shared by their ex-partner with peers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technology assisted sexual blackmail&lt;/strong&gt;  Sexual imagery of a child is obtained via technology and then used as leverage in sexual abuse, which may be either technical assisted, offline or both; for example, a young person shares a sexual image with a person via technology; this person (the abuser) then threatens to share this imagery if the young person does not produce further sexual images or comply with offline abuse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Offline contact child sexual exploitation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt; commissioned via technology - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;For example, perpetrators using technology to direct perpetrators who are physically with the child to commit abusive acts (for example, perpetrators in the UK watching and directing live streamed sexual abuse of children by perpetrators in another part of the world).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Added concerns of modern technology&lt;u&gt; &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perpetrators have many different online forums by which to contact children &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;and young people, whether they are known to them or not. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;As they have a &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;constant way of keeping in contact &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;with the young person, technology helps to keep the abuse going and can also be a means to escalate by using blackmail to share images or pass on information through video calling, skype etc. which are free. Therefore young people can be much more easily contacted. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sometimes young people might not be aware they are being groomed and can believe that they&amp;apos;re in a relationship with girlfriend or boyfriend.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Lowered inhibitions &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;There is a sense from some young people that had abusive individuals asked them to carry out their requests offline, they would not have complied. In other words, the online medium worked to lower their inhibitions or disguise abusive dynamics and threat.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Control of the night time space&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Perpetrators regularly contacting the victim during the night&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Increases perpetrators control over the victim and their immersion into their life&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Strategy to maintain the abusive situation by heightening the impact on the victim though increased fear, tiredness and concentration difficulties. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Concerns (cont.)&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Increased use of emotional blackmail&lt;/strong&gt; possibly because it&amp;apos;s harder to physically intimidate online &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Wider audience for re-victimisation: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Images being shared&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Victims not knowing who had seen them or when they may re-appear&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Self-blame related to sharing images and complying to with offenders requests&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responses of others &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responses of others &lt;/strong&gt;- Some young people feel that the impact of the abuse was minimised, or not considered to be such an ordeal, if it had not resulted in contact abuse.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Victims report that responses from parents and professionals is not always helpful&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;This piece of research suggests that professionals had a lack of understanding around technology assisted sexual abuse which can lead to victims feeling/being blamed for it and its impact being minimised.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Victims who received therapy after the abuse described positive experiences, increased being helped to recognise self-worth, and move away from self-blame and shame. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;This video clip tells the story of how a young girl is groomed online. Click on the link to view: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot;   href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KHF3TC0KCjU&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0563c1&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KHF3TC0KCjU&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Definitions - Sextortion&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Sextortion&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Is when someone talks you into exposing yourself on web cam after which they extort you, i.e. pressurise or blackmail you to do things you don&amp;apos;t want to, or to give them money. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Criminals operating abroad often commit these crimes. They think that distance and the anonymity the internet can provide will prevent their identification and capture  that is not true, in many cases they can be identified and stopped.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The key is early reporting facilitating early intervention and support. Whilst this crime is most often targeted at adults, children can and are caught up in the scam. When they are, it is crucial that they tell someone and are properly supported when they do so. A local example is of a young Edinburgh man took his own life due to being sextorted  as he felt too ashamed to ask for help.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Definitions - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Radicalisation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;Adolescence is a stage when young people begin to question their identities and sense of belonging. They start to push against boundaries and look for something to identify with. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Specific vulnerabilities may include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Young people who feel a sense of injustice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Feel marginalised within society or their community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Who have experienced bullying or racism. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Organisations looking to recruit people will try to exploit the above vulnerabilities in young people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Signs to look out for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Signs to look out for: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;(Be mindful that &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;many of the signs are common teenage behaviours)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Young person can start to isolate themselves from people/ friends they previously associated with.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Young person starts to show a conviction that their religion, culture or beliefs are under threat or being treated unfairly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Choosing to spend less time with family.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Young person is speaking in a way you don&amp;apos;t recognise  not using own words and sounding scripted. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;May appear more agitated discussing their views or refuse to discuss certain views.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;More secretive, especially around internet use. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Sites like Facebook, ASK FM and Twitter can be used by extremists looking to identify and target young people.&#160; Once they have established contact the young people are often asked to continue discussions on less main stream platforms such as Kick Messenger, whisper, Yik Yak or Omegle that can give a greater degree of anonymity and can be less easy to monitor.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Sometimes young people may have met the person, through friends or associates. The internet then provides the extremist a medium through which to build a rapport with the YP and begin to influence their thinking. Often young people may regard the person as their friend and will not recognise that their thoughts are being shaped and manipulated by them. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact on Behaviours and Wellbeing&lt;u&gt; &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Finger on the pulse  share all culture &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;- most young people today are comfortable with recording their entire lives on-line. This could include uploading and sharing photos, status messages (single/ in a relationship), how they are feeling, what they are doing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;It can create an environment where young people make impulsive decisions  click before they think  without thinking about the possible consequences &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;A click away from doing something digitally that they wouldn&amp;apos;t do in the &amp;apos;real world&amp;apos;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Puts pressure on children and young people to be constantly alert and available  they don&amp;apos;t want to miss out or be rejected from the chat.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Numbers game  Likes, loves and shares are the currency of social media. They quantify&#160;the popularity of a profile, image, video or status.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The number of likes on social media can have significant effect on people&amp;apos;s self-esteem /status within their peer group.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;More likes leads many&#160; young person to feel more endorsed and accepted by their peers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;What happens when the likes don&amp;apos;t rack up? Receiving fewer likes is likely to leave a person feel rejected&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An American study &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;An American study showed that a greater sense of &amp;apos;purpose&amp;apos; a person felt they had in life, the less affected they were by the amount of likes they received online. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;People who felt a greater amount of &amp;apos;purpose&amp;apos; were&#160;less rewarded and validated&#160;by many likes but&#160;also less negatively affected&#160;by few likes and negative comments.  can be related to achievements such as doing well in school or sports or having good friends, family and support.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;This suggests that children from more adverse backgrounds or with self-esteem/ mental health / confidence issues are likely to experience online rejection more negatively.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
This means that having a strong sense of well-being and worthiness offline could help to mediate the potential effects of social media.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Pressure to always look good  value placed on appearance and attractiveness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;73% of 8-12 year olds and 95% of 13-17 year olds studied had shared selfies on line.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;2 in 5 said they had received negative comments on a photo they had posted  can have a real impact on young person&amp;apos;s expression&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;On average young people take 12 selfies before they are happy to post one online&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;43% said they worry about how attractive they look when they share photos online&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;45% have used a filter in the last year to make themselves look better  particularly the case with 13-17 year old girls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;61% of 13-17 year old girls worried about how attractive their online pictures look&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;47% have felt sad about their looks after seeing a particular image or video online&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Body image  reports in 2015 that hospital admissions of teenagers with eating disorders nearly doubled in 3 years. The Royal College of Psychiatrists research showed the internet/social media had a part to play as young people exposed to images of perfect bodies constantly&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Further Pressures&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pressures on keeping up&lt;/strong&gt;  The nature of social media is such that information is constantly refreshed/updated and children and young people are worried about &amp;apos;missing out&amp;apos; or being rejected.&#160; Parental efforts to limit online time can often lead to confrontation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Impact on sleep and night time space&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Receptors in the eyes react to the blue light in electronic screens and this can affect melatonin production and sleep&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Constant need to be in contact&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Impact on family life&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;Parents can struggle to enforce boundaries&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;Children wanting latest gadgets and mobiles&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Vulnerable in real life &#160;= Vulnerable on the internet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Teenagers with pre-existing vulnerabilities of low self-esteem, psychological problems, and problematic relationships with parents or learning difficulties are more likely to be unable to adopt appropriate coping strategies whilst online and are the ones most likely to comply with the online offender&amp;apos;s requests to engage (Vandoninck et al., 2015). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sex, Relationships and the Internet&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;It is normal for children and young people to be curious about sex either &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;previously talking to each other and or with older siblings. It is natural for children and young people to push boundaries and explore, however, there are associated risks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;Platform for exploring sex  &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;In the UK, adult video on demand websites are regulated, and sites must keep explicit sexual images out of reach of under 18&amp;apos;s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;HOWEVER, the internet is global and websites from other countries, who are not subject to regulation, can be accessed from the UK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Children and young people may stumble across content online or actively search for sexual content which isn&amp;apos;t appropriate for their age.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sex, Relationships and the Internet (cont.)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

