&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;Over half of 11-16 year olds in a study by the Safe Internet Centre said they had been exposed to online pornography  Many reported being upset by the images they saw&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;A study by the NSPCC found that children were as likely to see pornography for the first time via &amp;apos;pop ups&amp;apos; as to search for it deliberately or be shown by others&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Once they had seen online pornography (either intentionally or not)&#160; - study showed 59% of&#160; boys and 40% of girls continued to view it&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Online it is easy to quickly access a wide variety of pornographic content including hard-core and extreme images and videos&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;NSPCC study  53% of boys and 39% of girls thought the pornography they had viewed online was realistic with some saying that it had given them ideas about sexual practices they wanted to act out/ try&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Pornography rarely presents sex in the context of a loving relationship and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;There is concern that early exposure to hard core pornography could give young people unhealthy views about the opposite sex and what they can expect from them.&lt;br /&gt;
	Researcher Martin Flood, &amp;apos;&lt;em&gt;pornography is a poor, and indeed dangerous, sex educator&amp;apos;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
