&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;If one party is an adult (over 16/18) and the other is a child, then the matter is child protection and other social work and police should be involved. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;If both parties are children and young people. The general guide is that professionals can use their professional&amp;apos;s judgement when faced with sexual relationships between young people when the age difference does not exceed two years if it&amp;apos;s in the context of a consenting relationship. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Whatever the circumstance, young people need to know that it is a criminal offence to distribute indecent images of anyone under the age 16 (including themselves).&#160; Notwithstanding this, it is recognised that in some situations education and guidance is far more appropriate, constructive and child centred than criminalising young people&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Where there are any indications of coercion, blackmail and/or a power imbalance, concerns should be discussed with social work or police. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;Live streaming is highly appealing to children and young people as it offers the opportunity for them to be a creator, a presenter and to be seen by a potentially huge audience, potentially thousands. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;We know that for adolescents, self-expression/self-presentation is really important, so sharing something and having hundreds/thousands people show an interest, can feel like the ultimate confidence and ego boost. The immediacy of live streaming combined with the pleasure of affirmation satisfies some of the developmental needs and desires that children and young people experience during adolescence.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Anyone with a camera enabled device and access to the internet can share a live video &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Live  shown in real time. There is no opportunity to edit or stop and think before things are posted&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Some apps allow viewers to comment on a live video as its broadcast&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Often the person in the video can read the comments as they are live streaming and feel pressured to respond&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Children and young people need to be warned of the risks and told to stop and tell someone if anyone asks them to take off clothing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Sharing unedited videos over the internet in &amp;apos;real time&amp;apos;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Unmoderated, unrehearsed and unpredictable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Young people can act on impulse and not consider consequences&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;May be accidentally exposed to inappropriate content&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Can be used by adult offenders to use tricks and dares to coerce young people into performing acts that may involve nudity &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cyber Bullying&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;Dangerous phenomenon&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;With online technologies accessible 24 hours a day, cyberbullying can be relentless. It can also intrude on spaces that were previously personal, for example at home; it can feel that there is no escape from it. A variety of psychological and social impacts have been identified as a result of cyber bullying. This can include: &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Emotional distress&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Anxiety, loneliness and depression&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Suicidal ideation and self-harm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;tab-stops: list 36.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Research suggests that a large proportion of cyber bullying or online harassment is focussed on identity related characteristics &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Sexual orientation &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Race, Religion &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Disability &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Gender identity &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Gender&#160; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Often judged on their looks &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Girls more likely to be referred to negatively or demandingly regarding &amp;apos; &lt;strong&gt;&amp;apos;sex- ubut -uality&amp;apos; &lt;/strong&gt;i.e. referred to as sluts etc. or referred to as sexual objects&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;A study by the UK Council for Child Internet Safety (2018) found 28% of 11-16 year olds reported having been upset when using a social networking site last year. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Bullying is one of the most common reasons why children contact Childline. There was a 13% rise from the previous year. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Children and Young people report being unsure about the action taken when they report cyber bullying to social media platforms. Some reported their concerns were not taken seriously.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;CYBERMENTORS&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;is&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt; an online counselling service with a difference; the counsellors are&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt; also children and young people. This site has proved very popular and offers practical advice.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;tab-stops: list 36.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indecent Images of Children &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: circle;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;It is an offence to take, distribute or have in your possession an indecent image of a child under the age of 18. Civic Government (Scotland) Act 1982 Section 52.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Voyeurism&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: circle;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;It is an offence to observe, record or distribute images of a person doing a private act (including nudity/in underwear) without their consent. Sexual Offences (Scotland) Act 2009 Section 9.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stalking&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: circle;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Includes publishing any statement relating to a person or purporting to originate from that person, or from any other person, that causes them to feel alarm Criminal Justice and Licensing (Scotland) Act 2010&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does the law say? (cont.)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Coercing a person into looking at a sexual image&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;It is an offence to make someone else look at a sexual image without their consent Sexual Offences (Scotland) Act 2009 Section 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communicating &#160;Indecently&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: circle;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;It is an offence to make someone else see written sexual communication, or hear verbal sexual communication without their consent Sexual Offences (Scotland) Act 2009 Section 7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;Threatening or upsetting messaging&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;It is an offence to send a message which is grossly offensive or of an indecent obscene or menacing character. Communications Act 2003 Section 127&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&#160;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;Efforts to develop children and young people&amp;apos;s digital resilience should focus on critical ability and technical competency in order to support children and young people in becoming active agents in their own protection and safety. Make sure they have technical safeguards in place, however; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;We also have to accept that children can learn to by pass them &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;They do not protect children from many of the various risks of being online&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;We need to prepare our children to have the skills and coping strategies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;tab-stops: list 36.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital resilience&lt;/strong&gt; is about having appropriate coping strategies and learning to adjust responses according to situations&#160; Feeling able to seek help and support and knowing where to go. Knowing about potential consequences of your own actions in order for children to regulate their own online behaviours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 8pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;Support around self-esteem and emotional resilience is also important to help them maintain perspective in an environment where looks and body image are disproportionally focussed on. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%;&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Calibri&quot;&gt;The responses when children do get things wrong must be calm and supportive so that they will not be discouraged from seeking support in the future; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Put safeguards in place&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Put on parental controls onto smart phones as well as computers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Set rules and boundaries at the start&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Ensure all devices are handed in to parent/carer at bed time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Show interest in the social media your child is using&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Install app on your phone to get an idea of what&amp;apos;s going on&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Become your child&amp;apos;s online friend&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Do not show disapproval or shock if your child discloses something to you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sources of information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

